[[File:Alba de América.jpg|thumbnail|right|Alba de America]]'''Antonio Brugada''' (1804 – 1863) was a Spanish painter. Brugada is best known for his dramatic seascapes.
Brugada was a friend of [[Francisco Goya]], and was instrumental in [[cataloging]], and identifying some of the mythological figures in Goya's c. 1823 "[[Black paintings]]" series.<ref>Weisberg, Gabriel P. in ''Twenty-first-century Perspectives on Nineteenth-century Art''. University of Delaware Press, 2008. {{ISBN|0-87413-011-5}}</ref>
