{{Infobox philosopher |region = [[Western philosophy]] |era = [[Contemporary philosophy]] |image = |name = Timothy Shanahan |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1960|12|22}} |birth_place = |alma_mater = [[University of Notre Dame]] |school_tradition = [[Analytic philosophy|Analytic]] |main_interests = [[philosophy of science]], [[philosophy of film]] |notable_ideas = |influences = |influenced = }}
'''Timothy Shanahan''' (born December 22, 1960) is an American philosopher and Professor of [[Philosophy]] at [[Loyola Marymount University]]. He is known for his research on [[philosophy of science]], [[philosophy and film]], and the [[morality of terrorism]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Weber|first1=Bruce|title=Review of Charles Darwin|url=http://ndpr.nd.edu/news/charles-darwin/|website=Notre Dame Philosophical Reviews|accessdate=13 October 2017|date=14 August 2008}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Depew|first1=David|title=Review of The Evolution of Darwinism|url=http://ndpr.nd.edu/news/the-evolution-of-darwinism/|website=[[Notre Dame Philosophical Reviews]]|accessdate=13 October 2017|date=8 January 2005}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Philosophy and Blade Runner, by Timothy Shanahan|url=https://www.timeshighereducation.com/books/philosophy-and-blade-runner-by-timothy-shanahan/2015320.article|website=[[Times Higher Education]] (THE)|accessdate=13 October 2017|language=en|date=28 August 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=[[Keith Dromm]]|title=Review of Philosophy and Blade Runner|url=http://www.keithdromm.com/2016/03/03/review-of-philosophy-and-blade-runner/|accessdate=13 October 2017|date=3 March 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Read|first1=Rupert|last2=Goodenough|first2=Jerry|title=Timothy Shanahan (2014), Philosophy and Blade Runner, Basingstoke: Palgrave Macmillan. 240pp.|url=http://www.film-philosophy.com/index.php/f-p/article/view/1133|website=[[Film-Philosophy]]|accessdate=13 October 2017|date=20 January 2016}}</ref>
==Books== * ''Reason and Insight: Western and Eastern Perspectives on the Pursuit of Moral Wisdom'', 2nd edition (Belmont, CA: Wadsworth, 2003). * ''The Evolution of Darwinism: Selection, Adaptation, and Progress in Evolutionary Biology'' (New York: Cambridge University Press, 2004). * ''Philosophy 9/11: Thinking about the War on Terrorism'' (Chicago: Open Court, 2005). * ''The Provisional Irish Republican Army and the Morality of Terrorism'' (Edinburgh: Edinburgh University Press, 2009). * ''Philosophy and Blade Runner'' (Houndsmills: Palgrave McMillan, 2014).
